
1 -> git clone <repo>

2 -> cd <proj_dir>

3 -> npm install     

<<---------- Build project -------->>
     
       ðŸ’  cd <proj_dir>

       ðŸ’  open another terminal and run 'npm run build'

       ðŸ’  '/dist' folder will be generated in root-directory where all your node transpiled and minified node modules will be.

       ðŸ’  Now cd<testing_project> to the desired project you wanna test.

       ðŸ’  Then run npm link maxtap_plugin_dev : It links your dev project files and folders to test project


       ðŸ’  import {Component} from 'maxtap_plugin_dev'
              window.addEventLister('load',()=>{
                     new Component({content_id:'content_id'}).init()
              })
       
       ðŸ’  Now if you update or change your files in proj_dir it reflects in your test project

       ------ Classic web

           cd <proj_dir>
           cd examples/classic_web
           run some server to host index.html 

           ------ Recommended to use parcel 

            ðŸ’  Run -> npm i -g parcel -> Install parcel to your global node_modules.
            
            ðŸ’  Run -> parcel src/index.html -> It creates dist folder in your project root dir where all your html,js,css,static files are being served.
    
       ------ ReactJs

           cd <proj_dir>
           cd examples/reactjs
           npm install
           npm start
    
       ------ NextJs
           cd <proj_dir>
           cd examples/nextjs
           npm install 
           npm run dev

